                            <comment id="15283627" author="jking3" created="Sat, 14 May 2016 17:47:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think this is related to your changes, but you can probably fix it faster than I can.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15322843" author="nsuke" created="Thu, 9 Jun 2016 16:45:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This does not seem to be reproducible.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://ci.appveyor.com/project/ApacheSoftwareFoundation/thrift/history&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://ci.appveyor.com/project/ApacheSoftwareFoundation/thrift/history&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The true problem for this kind of failures might be that no one has the simple &quot;rebuild this job&quot; button for apache&apos;s Appveyor and Travis-CI account.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15322845" author="jking3" created="Thu, 9 Jun 2016 16:48:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue here is out of our control.  Some of the sourceforge mirrors have purged older stuff.  When I put the link into a browser and then clicked on the &quot;Direct Link&quot;, it came back &quot;not found&quot;.  I reloaded and did it again, and I got another mirror, and it succeeded.  That&apos;s rather unfortunate.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15322861" author="nsuke" created="Thu, 9 Jun 2016 17:00:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah, I see. Maybe the chocolatey package people have fixed the download location since then.&lt;br/&gt;
Anyway, I guess we can leave it as is unless the problem re-emerges and persists.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15329392" author="jking3" created="Tue, 14 Jun 2016 12:19:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This busted &lt;a href=&quot;https://ci.appveyor.com/project/ApacheSoftwareFoundation/thrift/build/364&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://ci.appveyor.com/project/ApacheSoftwareFoundation/thrift/build/364&lt;/a&gt; which was a build for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3038&quot; title=&quot;Use of volatile in cpp library&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-3038&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-3038&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  Two other builds succeeded.  1 out of 3 builds failing is not something we can tolerate.  We need a more stable location from which to download this package.  Perhaps instead of letting sourceforge pick a mirror, we pick a mirror and code it into the build?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15335089" author="jking3" created="Fri, 17 Jun 2016 00:35:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;slproweb.com is not responsive right now, and it caused a build failure for the pull request on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3825&quot; title=&quot;Javascript test dependency is no longer available&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-3825&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-3825&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1029&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1029&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have to recommend again that we find a more stable way to provide dependenct packages to our build process.&lt;br/&gt;
Is there any way we can get the binaries on an apache server so that we know we&apos;ll be able to download them?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15521072" author="githubbot" created="Sun, 25 Sep 2016 16:30:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user nsuke opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1095&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1095&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3826&quot; title=&quot;Appveyor builds cannot download winflexbison properly&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-3826&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-3826&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Appveyor builds cannot download winflexbison properly&lt;/p&gt;



